comments.body:
Ouch, that was a serious problem with the fuzz test.

I've instead replaced it with

```c++
    LIMITED_WHILE(provider.remaining_bytes(), 1000) {
        CallOneOf(provider,
            // (Try to) give the next message to the transport.
            [&] { new_msg_fn(0); },
            [&] { new_msg_fn(1); },
            // (Try to) send some bytes from the transport to the network.
            [&] { send_fn(0); },
            [&] { send_fn(1); },
            // (Try to) receive bytes from the network, converting to messages.
            [&] { recv_fn(0); },
            [&] { recv_fn(1); }
        );
    }
```

which is hopefully as clear as your suggestion, but doesn't waste 2 bytes of input to pick one of 6 values.

