comments.body:
I would use `data_in_transport` instead of `_data_left` (see https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/28165#discussion_r1298717971).

And then drop `data_left = _data_left;`. 

Then below:

```cpp
bool message_queue_empty = it == node.vSendMsg.end()`
if (data_in_transport || !message_queue_empty) {
  flags |= MSG_MORE;
```

And:

```
// couldn't send anything at all
if (!data.empty()) {
  data_in_transport = true
}
```

And then finally return `!message_queue_empty || data_in_transport` instead of `data_left`.

